mathematics, living entities and systems can be dealt with only as if their "architecture" or "design" is based on the principle of non-contradiction, which is true only for non-living entities. This distortion explains our many crises. Vanderburg begins to explore the limits of discipline-based approaches, which guides the way toward developing complementary ones capable of transcending these limits. It is no different from a carpenter going beyond the limits of his hammer by reaching for other tools. As we grapple with everything from the impacts of social media, the ongoing climate crisis, and divisive political ideologies, Rescuing Humanity reveals that our civilization must learn to do the equivalent if humans and other living things are to continue making earth a home.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivilization, Moderny21st century. 0aHumanity. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Technology Studies.2bisacsh  aSTEM.  abiosphere interactions.  acultural anthropology.  acultural history.  acultural studies.  aculture.  aeconomics.  amedia studies.  aphilosophy.  ascience.  asociety.  asurveillance.  atechnology of religion.  atechnology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195840uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148755317340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487553173423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487553173/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles